  <body>
   <p>More than $625,000 was collected by the Associated Jewish Charities of Chicago last year, according to the report at the annual meeting.</p>
   <p>Among the institutions which benefitted from this fund were - The Jewish Aid Society, $150,000, the Michael Reese Hospital, $160,000, and the Jewish Home Finding Society, $70,000.</p>
